      "content": "```python\ndef find_prime_factors(n):\n    factors = []\n    d = 2\n    temp = n\n    while temp > 1:\n        while temp % d == 0:\n            factors.append(d)\n            temp //= d\n        d += 1\n        if d * d > temp:\n            if temp > 1:\n                factors.append(temp)\n            break\n    return factors\n```\nThis version breaks early once `d*d > temp`, avoiding unnecessary iterations for large inputs. It still returns the same factors but runs in O(√n) instead of O(n).",
